Asia
---
- Bangladesh (Dhaka). 15 Aug 2011. Dengue is increasing alarmingly in
Dhaka city with the highest number of 473 cases reported up to 11 Aug
2011.
http://www.gulf-times.com/site/topics/article.asp?cu_no=2&item_no=452657&version=1&template_id=44&parent_id=24

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Bangladesh can be accessed
at http://healthmap.org/r/0AzT. - Mod.TY]

- Pakistan (Punjab province). 12 Aug 2011. 8 new cases of dengue have
been reported following diagnosis in Lahore during the last 24 hours.
5 patients belonged to Lahore, while the remaining 3 hailed from other
districts of the province. The total number of patients of dengue
fever reported from the whole province during the last 7 months has
reached 65 out of which 49 have been reported from Lahore.
http://www.thenews.com.pk/TodaysPrintDetail.aspx?ID=62461&Cat=5&dt=8/12/2011

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Punjab province can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/0cco. - Mod.TY]

- Pakistan (Karachi, Sindh province). 9 Aug 2011. At least 4 dengue
viral fever cases have been reported from Karachi and all 4 patients
are admitted in private hospitals. In-charge Dengue Surveillance Cell
of Sindh Health Department, Dr Suresh Kumar, said Monday [8 Aug 2011]
that 4 cases of dengue viral fever had been confirmed.
http://www.dailytimes.com.pk/default.asp?page=2011%5C08%5C09%5Cstory_9-8-2011_pg12_16

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Sindh province can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/02SY. - Mod.TY]

- India (Goa). 14 Aug 2011. From January-12 Aug 2011, about 513
persons were tested for dengue, of which 7 were tested positive.
According to DHS officials, the outbreak of vector borne diseases
coincides with monsoon and post-monsoon periods.
http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-08-14/goa/29886078_1_chikungunya-dengue-mosquito-bites

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Goa can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/018C. - Mod.TY]

- India (Orissa state). 16 Aug 2011. 2 more dengue deaths were
reported in the state today [16 Aug 2011] -- at SCB Medical College
and Hospital in Cuttack and Kalinga Hospital in Bhubaneswar -- taking
the toll to 14 so far. According to officials of the health
department, 195 of the 541 blood samples sent so far have tested
positive for the disease [virus]. Though the fever was earlier
confined to Angul, Dhenkanal, and Sundargarh, it has now spread to 16
districts, including Balasore, Khurda, Cuttack, and Kalahandi.
http://www.indianexpress.com/news/2-more-dengue-deaths-in-Orissa--toll-up-to-14/832419/

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Orissa state can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/07gd. - Mod.TY]

- India (Delhi). 9 Aug 2011. 10 new cases of dengue have been reported
in Delhi in the last week. With this the total number of such cases
this season has gone up to 25, Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD)
said. One person died of dengue last month [July 2011].
http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-08-09/delhi/29867998_1_dengue-cases-of-water-borne-diseases-vector-borne-diseases-control-programme

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of India showing the location
of Delhi can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/01Jf. - Mod.TY]

- Nepal (Chitwan district). 9 Aug 2011. 7 more cases of dengue have
been found in the past 3 weeks in Chitwan district according to the
District Public Health Office (DPHO). A total of 735 dengue cases and
4 deaths were confirmed in Chitwan in 2067 BS [April 2010-April 2011].
The total number of dengue cases in the district has reached 17 after
the Nepali New Year [16 Apr 2011].
http://www.myrepublica.com/portal/index.php?action=news_details&news_id=34493

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Nepal can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/18Bz. - Mod.TY]

- Philippines.(national). 14 Aug 2011. Dengue is wreaking havoc in
large areas of the Philippines and afflicted more than 46 000 people
in the last 7 months, a top Department of Health (DoH) official
reported on Saturday [13 Aug 2011]. Of the total for the period from 1
Jan-6 Aug [2011], Dr Eric Tayag, the chief of the DoH Epidemiology
Center, said dengue claimed the lives 267 people who were mostly
children. But even more alarming, Tayag added, was that the 6000 new
patients were reported in the last 2 weeks, with the provinces of La
Union and Ilocos Sur in Northern Luzon declaring a state of calamity
due to upsurge in the number of dengue cases.
http://gulftoday.ae/portal/414f7cab-de9b-4e74-a6b1-916ac9b0b4fb.aspx

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the Philippines can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/00bk. - Mod.TY]

- Philippines (Southwestern Mindanao). 8 Aug 2011. Jane Ventura,
health education officer of the Department of Health (DOH)-Region 12
[Southwestern Mindanao], said the agency's regional epidemiology and
surveillance unit (RESU) reported that dengue cases in the region from
January to July this year [2011] has so far reached 1192, increasing
by 510 cases since the onset of the rainy season in early June. She
said the total number of dengue cases have gone down by 83 per cent
compared to last year [2010], but the confirmed deaths have almost
doubled in just about a month or from 6 cases last June 25 to 11 cases
as of the last week of July.
http://www.mindanews.com/top-stories/2011/08/08/dengue-deaths-in-r-12-now-11/

[A map showing the location of Mindanao can be accessed at
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mindanao. - Mod.TY]

- Philippines (Laoag city, Ilocos Norte province). 6 Aug 2011.
According to the city health office, 186 residents have fallen ill due
to dengue from January to July this year [2011]. The province recorded
5 dengue-related deaths this year. City health officer Renato Mateo,
however, said the current number of dengue cases was still lower than
what was reported during the same period last year.
http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/37361/dengue-cases-raise-alert-levels-in-laoag-city

[5 dengue deaths of 186 cases is an extraordinarily high mortality
rate, leading one to suspect that the number of dengue fever cases is
underreported.
A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of Laoag
city can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/18BB. - Mod.TY]

- Singapore. 6 Aug 2011. The number of weekly dengue cases has taken a
dip since fears of a major dengue epidemic surfaced in July [2011].
According to numbers from the National Environment Agency, the latest
weekly figures of 179 dengue cases as of 3 pm [Fri 5 Aug 2011] is a
drop from the previous number of 263 cases. There were 13 new dengue
cases as of 3 pm yesterday [Fri 5 Aug 2011]. In comparison, 29 new
dengue cases were reported on Thursday [4 Aug 2011].
http://www.todayonline.com/Singapore/EDC110806-0000197/Fall-in-weekly-dengue-cases

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Singapore can be accessed
at http://healthmap.org/r/18BC. - Mod.TY]

Caribbean
---
- Bahamas. 11 Aug 2011. The Bahamas has now broken its record for the
number of dengue fever cases reported during the seasonal outbreaks,
with more than 1500 confirmed cases, according to the Minister of
Health, Dr Hubert Minnis. He added that the inordinate number of cases
this year [2011] has stretched the public health care system to the
limit, as hundreds of people have been showing up at public clinics
across the island with symptoms of dengue fever.
http://www.thenassauguardian.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=12078&Itemid=27

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the Bahamas can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/15NJ. - Mod.TY]

- Bahamas. 16 Aug 2011. While health officials tackle the dengue fever
outbreak in the capital, Minister of Health Hubert Minnis revealed
yesterday that, aside from the two "imported" cases, Grand Bahama has
no dengue problem. "You only had 2 cases there. Both were imported
from Nassau," he told The Freeport News Sunday [14 Aug 2011]. The 2
individuals, he explained, had travelled from New Providence where it
is believed they became infected. However, they were diagnosed with
the virus in Grand Bahama where they were subsequently treated.
http://freeport.nassauguardian.net/national_local/300775962848647.php.

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the Bahamas can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/15NJ. The Commonwealth of the
Bahamas is made up of 29 islands with the major islands
population-wise being New Providence Island (Nassau & Paradise Island)
& the Grand Bahamas (Freeport). It is not surprising to hear that the
major outbreak is on the most populous island. - Mod.MPP]

- Trinidad & Tobago. 12 Aug 2011. The number of reported dengue cases,
as of 30 Jul [2011], is 1639, with the highest number reported in
Tobago. The statistics were provided yesterday [11 Aug 2011] by Health
Minister Dr Fuad Khan at yesterday's launch of the national campaign.
http://www.guardian.co.tt/news/2011/08/12/1639-cases-dengue-so-far

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Trinidad & Tobago can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/18BD. - Mod.TY]

Latin America
---
- Mexico (Huejutla, Hidalgo state). 10 Aug 2011. Officials in the
vector area of Health Jurisdiction 10, based in Huejutla, confirmed 3
dengue fever cases in the Huasteca region of Hidalgo, which they
assure will be attended to, to avoid an outbreak. They explained that
with the rains that have occurred in recent months, the mosquito
vector that transmits the disease [virus] (_Aedes aegypti_) has
accelerated its proliferation.
http://www.oem.com.mx/elsoldehidalgo/notas/n2180279.htm [in Spanish,
trans. Mod.TY]

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Mexico can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/17RO. - Mod.TY]

- Brazil (Ribeirao Preto, Sao Paulo state). 11 Aug 2011. This year
[2011], there have now been more than 15 000 dengue cases registered.
The tests now confirm that 100 percent of the cases are due to dengue
[virus] type 1, indicating that it is the only virus type
circulating.
http://eptv.globo.com/ribeiraopreto/noticias/NOT,2,2,363054,Ribeirao+Preto+Infectologistas+aumento+casos+dengue+hemorragica.aspx
[in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY]

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Sao Paulo state can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/0IpF. - Mod.TY]

- Brazil (Fortaleza, Ceara state). 13 Aug 2011. Forteleza has
currently registered 25 115 dengue cases up to August [2011],
according to the state Secretariat of Health. This is almost 5 times
the total number of cases last year [2010] when there were 5433 dengue
cases. As of now in Ceara state there are 42 859 dengue cases with 54
fatalities and another 20 deaths under investigation.
http://diariodonordeste.globo.com/noticia.asp?codigo=324853&modulo=966
[in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY]

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Ceara state can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/00Sq. - Mod.TY]
